canonical:
  title: 爲某州守呈祭告使狀
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 雲霄承命原隰耀華行色所巡讙謠遍洽恭惟某官邈從天闕夙駕星軺載馳載驅信賢勞於王事克禋克祀亦與沐於神休燕及生民均蒙陰賜某等謬叨憂寄愧乏吏能自逖聽先聲願一得覯止見止及迫臨弊境實萬倍顚之倒之曁接淸塵粗伸素蘊
  rtl: true
  vertical: true
lzh_formatted:
  title: 爲某州守呈祭告使狀
  author: 李奎報
  language: lzh
  text: 雲霄承命。原隰耀華。行色所巡。讙謠遍洽。恭惟某官。邈從天闕。夙駕星軺。載馳載驅。信賢勞於王事。克禋克祀。亦與沐於神休。燕及生民。均蒙陰賜。某等謬叨憂寄。愧乏吏能。自逖聽先聲。願一得覯止見止。及迫臨弊境。實萬倍顚之倒之。曁接淸塵。粗伸素蘊。
korean:
  title: 위 모주수 정 제고사 장
  author: 이규보
  language: kor
  text: 천상에서 왕명을 받들고 머나먼 길에 영화를 빛내시니, 귀한 행차가 순찰하는 곳에 즐거운 노래가 두루 흡족합니다. 삼가 생각하건대, 모관(某官)은 멀리 조정으로부터 일찍이 성초(星軺 사신의 수레)를 타고서 말을 달려 참으로 나랏일에 부지런하고, 제사를 받들어 신의 아름다움에 젖어드니 즐거움이 민생에게 미쳐 골고루 음조를 입습니다. 모(某) 등은 그릇되게 외방을 맡아 다스림에, 수령의 역량이 부족한 것이 부끄러우며, 성화를 들을 길이 멀어짐으로부터 한번 얻어 뵙기를 원하던 차라, 폐읍(弊邑)에 왕림하게 되시니 실로 만배나 더 반갑게 환영하겠습니다. 청진(淸塵)을 접촉함에 미쳐 대략 소회를 아룁니다.
  url: https://db.itkc.or.kr/dir/item?itemId=BT#dir/node?dataId=ITKC_BT_1365A_0510_010_0480&viewSync=OT
  footnotes: []
english:
  title: Memorial Presented by a Prefect Regarding the Reception of an Envoy Bearing Sacrificial Proclamations
  author: Lee Gyu-bo
  language: eng
  text: |-
    From the heavens the royal mandate descends,
    illuminating the distant roads with splendor.
    Wherever your honorable procession traverses,
    the songs of the people ring out in joyful accord.

    With reverent contemplation, we observe how
    this eminent official journeys far from the imperial court,
    rising early to mount the envoy's chariot of stars,
    dashing swiftly in service to the throne.
    True to the kingdom's call, you labor steadfastly,
    performing the sacred rites with utmost devotion,
    receiving the blessings of heaven itself.
    Such favor extends to our people,
    who uniformly partake of heaven's gracious gifts.

    We humble administrators, unworthy of our charge,
    blush at our insufficient abilities.
    From afar, we yearned to hear of your renown,
    dreaming but once to glimpse your presence.
    Now that you grace our humble province,
    our joy multiplies a thousandfold—
    such longing finally fulfilled!

    As we now brush the dust of your journey,
    we offer these humble sentiments as tribute.
  footnotes:
  - key: ''
    value: 'Star-chariot (星軺): A traditional metaphor for an official envoy''s carriage, evoking both celestial dignity and swift passage.'
  - key: ''
    value: This is a formal memorial state document, a genre of official correspondence in classical Korean-Chinese literature, typically presented to accompany ceremonial occasions.
